There are a few ways to remove outside CSS styling from your index.cshtml in ASP.NET Core MVC:

1. Remove the external CSS file reference:
If your index.cshtml references an external CSS file, you can simply remove or comment out the link reference in the head section of your HTML:

```html
<head>
    <title>My Page</title>
    <!-- <link rel="stylesheet" href="external.css" /> -->
</head>
```

2. Use the style tag to override external CSS:
If you need to keep the external CSS file reference but want to remove specific styles, you can use the style tag to override them. You can add these style tags in the head section of your HTML, after the link reference to the external CSS file:

```html
<head>
    <title>My Page</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="external.css" />
    <style>
        /* Overrides the font-size and color from the external CSS */
        body {
            font-size: 16px;
            color: #000;
        }

        /* Removes the margin from any element with the class "no-margin" */
        .no-margin {
            margin: 0;
        }
    </style>
</head>
```

3. Use the !important rule to override styles:
If the external CSS styles are using the !important rule, you can use it as well to override those styles. The !important rule gives the style priority over any other style. You can add this rule to any CSS selector:

```html
<head>
    <title>My Page</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="external.css" />
    <style>
        /* Overrides the font-size and color from the external CSS */
        body {
            font-size: 16px !important;
            color: #000 !important;
        }

        /* Removes the margin from any element with the class "no-margin" */
        .no-margin {
            margin: 0 !important;
        }
    </style>
</head>
```

By using these methods, you can remove or override any external CSS styling in your index.cshtml file.

